        "Propagate HTTP write failures from upload handlers instead of dropping them.",
        "Normalize filesystem existence checks to treat non-`NotExist` errors as fatal for control decisions."
      ]
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "upload_response_write_errors_ignored",
      "summary": "Upload handler drops `ResponseWriter` write errors, losing transport failure context",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/importer/importer.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`sendUploadResponse` calls `w.WriteHeader` and `w.Write` but does not return or inspect write errors, and callers do not branch on failures after response write attempts."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Change `sendUploadResponse` to return an error and have `failUploadRequest`/`HTTPUploadHandler` handle it by logging and failing the request with a secondary server error fallback so callers can react consistently.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "error_consistency",
      "identifier": "fs_exists_check_ignores_non_notexist_errors",
      "summary": "Filesystem existence checks ignore non-`NotExist` errors and can misclassify error conditions as success",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/importer/importer.go",
        "goseg/system/disk.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`allChunksReceived` only treats `os.IsNotExist(err)` as an incomplete chunk signal and treats all other `os.Stat` errors as though the chunk exists.",
        "`CreateGroundSegFilesystem` loops until `os.Stat` is `os.IsNotExist`, which can silently continue on permission/I/O errors instead of failing fast."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a shared helper for path probes that returns an explicit error for any non-`NotExist` failure, and use it in import completion checks and disk path selection to stop workflows on filesystem anomalies.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "non_discriminating_fs_error_paths"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Transport response and filesystem existence checks rely on partial success assumptions that discard important error classes.",
      "Error strategy drift: some call sites treat only one error condition as actionable and silently continue for the rest."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "Upload API appears to succeed while clients receive truncated/undelivered responses",
      "Import completion may be triggered when chunk availability checks are unreliable due to unexpected FS errors"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": []
